1
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:18,211
[groaning]

2
00:01:23,883 --> 00:01:25,919
Cassandra was not the one.

3
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,787
It appears she was not.

4
00:01:27,787 --> 00:01:30,824
You’ll be entering
your 100th year.
We must find the one.

5
00:01:30,824 --> 00:01:33,059
I am more than aware of
what will happen if we do not.

6
00:01:33,059 --> 00:01:36,196
We don’t have much time.
You’ve got ancient blood that--

7
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,198
Thank you for
the reminder, Logan.

8
00:01:38,198 --> 00:01:40,567
I’m aware of my lineage
and what I must do.

9
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:42,769
Los Angeles.

10
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,272
The City of Angels.

11
00:01:45,272 --> 00:01:47,440
Let us hope that I find mine.

12
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:27,113
♪ I’ll make you burn,
then I’ll make you
fall asleep ♪

13
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:33,720
♪ You’ll feel dead
when you’re laying under me ♪

14
00:02:36,022 --> 00:02:39,459
♪ If I take a shot,
baby, will it sting? ♪

15
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:42,862
♪ Just turn me on,
and I’ll do my thing ♪

16
00:02:42,862 --> 00:02:47,701
♪ Won’t let you crash,
and I won’t let you bleed ♪

17
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:52,205
♪ You’re like a virus ♪

18
00:03:15,628 --> 00:03:16,730
Hey.

19
00:03:19,966 --> 00:03:22,001
Hey, let me help you with those.

20
00:03:22,001 --> 00:03:24,504
So, this is the place, huh?

21
00:03:25,839 --> 00:03:27,440
Yeah.

22
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:30,744
I know it’s not much,
but it does keep the rain out.

23
00:03:30,744 --> 00:03:32,479
I’m sorry.
I didn’t mean to be rude.

24
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:34,881
It’s just like the pictures
you sent me online.

25
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,416
Hey, no offense taken.

26
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:39,619
- Great first impression, huh?
- Yeah.

27
00:03:39,619 --> 00:03:41,755
- I’m Caleb.
- I’m Paul.

28
00:03:41,755 --> 00:03:43,556
It’s really nice
to finally meet you.

29
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:45,325
Let’s take your stuff inside
and get you settled,

30
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:46,726
and I’ll show you
around the place.

31
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:48,194
Sounds like a plan.

32
00:03:48,194 --> 00:03:50,730
Hey, dude, dude.
Not on the grass. Come on.

33
00:03:52,532 --> 00:03:55,135
Home sweet home.

34
00:03:55,135 --> 00:03:58,438
This place is really...

35
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:01,674
great.

36
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:04,677
Well, I mean,
it’s functional,

37
00:04:04,677 --> 00:04:07,113
but what more does
a college student need, right?

38
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:09,449
Not much more, I suppose.

39
00:04:09,449 --> 00:04:12,819
So, uh, first time
being away from home.

40
00:04:14,554 --> 00:04:17,724
I’ve been on my own
about two years now,

41
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:20,827
and I love my freedom.

42
00:04:22,162 --> 00:04:23,663
If you don’t mind my asking,

43
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:26,332
how did you find
such a great place so cheap?

44
00:04:26,332 --> 00:04:30,303
You know, I mean,
I have my connections.

45
00:04:30,303 --> 00:04:33,206
Actually, um, my parents
used to own this place,

46
00:04:33,206 --> 00:04:34,908
so it’s all paid for
free and clear.

47
00:04:34,908 --> 00:04:36,676
Pretty sweet deal.

48
00:04:36,676 --> 00:04:37,911
Yeah, no shit.

49
00:04:37,911 --> 00:04:39,779
Besides, I have no desire
to be anywhere else.

50
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:41,981
I’m a California boy
through and through.

51
00:04:41,981 --> 00:04:44,083
Sure beats living in Ohio.

52
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:45,752
Doesn’t it smell there?

53
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:47,220
Don’t remind me.

54
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:50,423
Let me take you to the bedroom.

55
00:05:02,869 --> 00:05:04,771
It’s really great-- you
letting me stay here for free.

56
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:08,107
Hey, like I said,
this place is all paid for,

57
00:05:08,107 --> 00:05:11,110
and utilities don’t cost much,
so you can pitch in with those.

58
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:12,745
Sounds more than fair.

59
00:05:12,745 --> 00:05:15,081
I was actually gonna
have some coffee.
Care to join me?

60
00:05:15,081 --> 00:05:17,784
I can show you
the neighborhood a bit.
My treat.

61
00:05:17,784 --> 00:05:19,686
That sounds nice.

62
00:05:19,686 --> 00:05:22,489
It’s a pretty
friendly neighborhood.

63
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:24,824
I can see that.
Quiet, too.

64
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:27,327
Yeah, and they’re
pretty receptive

65
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:29,829
to, uh,
all types of people.

66
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:31,631
Good to know.

67
00:05:41,107 --> 00:05:42,342
Not bad.

68
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:44,844
This was a really great idea.
Thanks.

69
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:47,680
Hey. My pleasure.

70
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,949
So, what did you do
in high school?

71
00:05:49,949 --> 00:05:51,518
Basketball? Football?

72
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:52,785
Swimming was my thing.

73
00:05:52,785 --> 00:05:54,854
All-state champ
three years in a row.

74
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:58,157
Impressive. You could be
the next Michael Phelps.

75
00:05:58,157 --> 00:06:00,426
I have hung up my Speedo.

76
00:06:00,426 --> 00:06:03,162
Focusing solely on academics.

77
00:06:03,162 --> 00:06:05,164
Mmm. A brainy jock.

78
00:06:05,164 --> 00:06:06,933
So few in existence.

79
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:11,237
Oh, we are a rare breed.

80
00:06:13,406 --> 00:06:14,874
[chuckles]

81
00:06:24,851 --> 00:06:28,788
Oh, another beautiful
California day.

82
00:06:28,788 --> 00:06:31,991
Even though I can’t
feel the heat of the sun,

83
00:06:31,991 --> 00:06:35,028
I’m so pleased that the myths
about vampires and the sun

84
00:06:35,028 --> 00:06:36,829
were just that-- myths.

85
00:06:36,829 --> 00:06:40,900
Yeah. Skin still tans
pretty well, too.

86
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:44,671
You two can be absolutely
ridiculous at times.

87
00:06:44,671 --> 00:06:47,540
Sorry, Logan, we’re not
as old and mature as you.

88
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:49,876
- Or as fat.
- Children.

89
00:06:49,876 --> 00:06:52,979
- Both of you.
- Forever and ever.

90
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:16,069
What did you see?

91
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:19,405
It was a person.
A male.

92
00:07:19,405 --> 00:07:21,908
Someone who will
cross our path?

93
00:07:21,908 --> 00:07:26,613
Yes. Someone who will be
very important to me.

94
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:28,281
- The one?
- Don’t be stupid.

95
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:31,517
- He found the one.
- Tara?

96
00:07:31,517 --> 00:07:33,419
I don’t know if she is.

97
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:37,357
What did he look like?

98
00:07:37,357 --> 00:07:40,960
I-- I cannot remember.

99
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:44,530
But I will know him again
if I see him.

100
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:47,066
I think there was a connection,

101
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:49,235
and I think he felt it, too.

102
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:52,038
- [snapping fingers]
- Are you okay?

103
00:07:53,539 --> 00:07:54,907
Are you okay?

104
00:07:56,442 --> 00:07:58,444
Yeah.

105
00:07:58,444 --> 00:08:00,913
That was really weird.

106
00:08:00,913 --> 00:08:02,882
Uh...

107
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:06,119
Sorry about that.

108
00:08:06,119 --> 00:08:08,221
Hey, it’s okay.

109
00:08:08,221 --> 00:08:10,490
But are you okay?

110
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,059
Um, what were we talking about?

111
00:08:13,059 --> 00:08:15,161
Classes tomorrow.

112
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:17,463
Great. I can’t believe
I just got here,

113
00:08:17,463 --> 00:08:19,799
and I have to jump
right back into classes.

114
00:08:19,799 --> 00:08:22,502
Are you sure you’re okay?

115
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,003
You look a little pale.

116
00:08:25,104 --> 00:08:27,073
I will be.
Maybe, just, um,

117
00:08:27,073 --> 00:08:29,742
rest a little
when we get back to the house.

118
00:08:29,742 --> 00:08:32,845
Okay. Um,
let’s head back then.

119
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:34,480
Come on.

120
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:20,393
Hello?

121
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:26,666
Who’s there?

122
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:38,211
I’ve seen you before.

123
00:09:38,211 --> 00:09:40,546
And I have seen you.

124
00:09:40,546 --> 00:09:42,548
Who are you?

125
00:09:42,548 --> 00:09:45,485
I would like to know
the same of you.

126
00:09:45,485 --> 00:09:49,021
I don’t understand
what’s going on.

127
00:09:49,021 --> 00:09:54,260
Dreams are often subject
to interpretation.

128
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:56,629
Is this a dream?

129
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:59,031
Would you prefer a nightmare?

130
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,667
No.

131
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:11,944
We’ll meet again.

132
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:21,788
- Morning.
- Hey. Morning.

133
00:10:23,656 --> 00:10:25,725
Coffee’s ready.

134
00:10:31,898 --> 00:10:33,466
Awkward.

135
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,501
Um, let me go
throw something on.

136
00:10:35,501 --> 00:10:38,437
Hey, it’s not a big deal for me
if it isn’t for you.

137
00:10:38,437 --> 00:10:41,007
We’re roommates, right?

138
00:10:41,007 --> 00:10:43,442
So, you ready
for your first day?

139
00:10:43,442 --> 00:10:47,079
I think so. I didn’t get
very much sleep last night.

140
00:10:47,079 --> 00:10:50,616
- Homesick?
- Nothing like that.

141
00:10:50,616 --> 00:10:53,152
I had a weird dream.

142
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:55,021
You remember any of it?

143
00:10:55,021 --> 00:10:56,722
I feel like
I should remember it,

144
00:10:56,722 --> 00:10:58,591
but every time I try,

145
00:10:58,591 --> 00:11:00,393
nothing comes to me.

146
00:11:00,393 --> 00:11:03,095
Well, you’ll have plenty
to take your mind off it today.

147
00:11:03,095 --> 00:11:05,464
I took the liberty of looking up
your classes online,

148
00:11:05,464 --> 00:11:07,033
and we have some
classes together.

149
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:08,534
Excellent.

150
00:11:08,534 --> 00:11:09,902
I hate being
in new situations

151
00:11:09,902 --> 00:11:12,505
with everybody staring at me.

152
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,640
Mmm.

153
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:12,198
So, how’s the first
few hours been?

154
00:12:12,198 --> 00:12:14,734
Pretty good, and I think
I’m getting into college life.

155
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,769
Ah. Just wait until
the parties start.

156
00:12:16,769 --> 00:12:18,404
That’s true college life.

157
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:20,139
♪ SOS ♪

158
00:12:20,139 --> 00:12:21,908
♪ SOS ♪

159
00:12:21,908 --> 00:12:25,778
♪ Doctor, doctor,
doctor, doctor ♪

160
00:12:25,778 --> 00:12:27,980
♪ In my chest ♪

161
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:29,615
♪ In my chest ♪

162
00:12:29,615 --> 00:12:32,285
♪ Monster, monster, monster ♪

163
00:12:32,285 --> 00:12:36,656
-♪ Send me an SOS ♪
-♪ SOS ♪

164
00:12:36,656 --> 00:12:38,190
♪ Send me a doctor ♪

165
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:39,992
Who are they?

166
00:12:39,992 --> 00:12:42,895
Um, I don’t know.

167
00:12:42,895 --> 00:12:45,331
I mean, I’ve never seen them
on campus before.

168
00:12:49,735 --> 00:12:52,471
Hi, my name’s Jasin.

169
00:12:52,471 --> 00:12:55,140
You’re new here,
aren’t you?

170
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,842
Just moved here yesterday.

171
00:12:56,842 --> 00:12:59,945
Hi, I’m Paul, his roommate.

172
00:13:01,046 --> 00:13:03,148
I did not mean
to come across forward.

173
00:13:03,148 --> 00:13:05,684
I fancy myself a welcome wagon
of sorts.

174
00:13:05,684 --> 00:13:08,353
It’s not a problem at all.

175
00:13:08,353 --> 00:13:12,124
How rude of me.
Paul, did you say?

176
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:14,092
Yeah.

177
00:13:16,161 --> 00:13:18,163
Let me introduce my brothers.

178
00:13:18,163 --> 00:13:21,466
This is Logan, Dane, and Adam.

179
00:13:21,466 --> 00:13:23,301
Brothers?

180
00:13:23,301 --> 00:13:25,337
Something like that.

181
00:13:25,337 --> 00:13:29,374
Hey, guys. I’m...Paul.

182
00:13:29,374 --> 00:13:32,077
They don’t say much.

183
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:36,214
I saw you in class
earlier today.

184
00:13:36,214 --> 00:13:39,885
It looks like
we’ll be seeing each other
every morning.

185
00:13:39,885 --> 00:13:42,387
I suppose so.

186
00:13:42,387 --> 00:13:45,190
Can I expect coffee
every morning?

187
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:46,925
You just never know.

188
00:13:46,925 --> 00:13:48,960
There you are.

189
00:13:52,898 --> 00:13:54,733
Hey, guys.

190
00:13:54,733 --> 00:13:57,269
So, who are your new friends?

191
00:13:57,269 --> 00:14:00,505
I am just neglecting
my manners completely today.

192
00:14:00,505 --> 00:14:03,308
I’m Caleb. This is Paul.

193
00:14:03,308 --> 00:14:06,411
I think you were in one of
my classes this morning.

194
00:14:06,411 --> 00:14:07,546
I’m Tara.

195
00:14:07,546 --> 00:14:09,414
[Paul]
Possibly. Was it psych?

196
00:14:09,414 --> 00:14:11,416
I thought you looked familiar.

197
00:14:11,416 --> 00:14:13,118
Yeah. Small world.

198
00:14:15,787 --> 00:14:18,356
So, will I see you tonight?

199
00:14:18,356 --> 00:14:20,325
Actually,
I was just getting ready

200
00:14:20,325 --> 00:14:21,760
to ask my new friend here

201
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:24,596
if he would like
a tour of the city.

202
00:14:26,098 --> 00:14:27,466
You’re new to L.A.?

203
00:14:27,466 --> 00:14:29,267
Fresh off the boat.

204
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:30,535
How about it, Caleb?

205
00:14:30,535 --> 00:14:33,105
Uh, yeah,
that would be great.

206
00:14:33,105 --> 00:14:36,141
Well, I suppose
I can take a rain check.

207
00:14:42,347 --> 00:14:45,317
We don’t have anything
planned this evening, do we?

208
00:14:45,317 --> 00:14:47,319
Um, no. No.

209
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:48,887
I mean, go have fun.

210
00:14:48,887 --> 00:14:51,790
Are you sure?
What if he came with us?

211
00:14:51,790 --> 00:14:53,325
Would that be okay?

212
00:14:53,325 --> 00:14:55,627
Go. I mean, I’ve seen the city
a thousand times.

213
00:14:55,627 --> 00:14:57,629
So, you know,
we’ll catch up later.

214
00:14:57,629 --> 00:15:00,065
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

215
00:15:00,065 --> 00:15:02,601
We are roommates, right?
We’ll be seeing each other
in no time.

216
00:15:02,601 --> 00:15:04,436
It’s bound to happen.

217
00:15:04,436 --> 00:15:06,772
So this evening.
I can pick you up.

218
00:15:06,772 --> 00:15:09,374
I don’t have a car,
so that would be great.

219
00:15:09,374 --> 00:15:10,742
Uh...

220
00:15:12,511 --> 00:15:15,714
Uh, here is where
I’ll be staying.

221
00:15:15,714 --> 00:15:17,716
I put my cell on there, too.

222
00:15:19,217 --> 00:15:20,519
Excellent.

223
00:15:22,454 --> 00:15:24,890
I think we should go anyway.
Your first class
is about to start.

224
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:26,591
Uh, we have this one
together, right?

225
00:15:26,591 --> 00:15:28,426
- Yeah.
- Uh, excellent.

226
00:15:28,426 --> 00:15:30,262
I’ll be there around 9:00.

227
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,798
I’ll see you this evening.

228
00:15:36,568 --> 00:15:38,670
That was interesting.

229
00:15:38,670 --> 00:15:40,105
I’m sorry?

230
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:42,073
He’s a fine catch
for sure, but...
[scoffs]

231
00:15:42,073 --> 00:15:45,310
- Let it be, Logan.
- Mind your own business, Adam.

232
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:48,447
Jasin finding the right one
is my business,
in case you’ve forgotten.

233
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:52,117
- We all need this.
- Remember, his fate
is our fate.

234
00:15:52,117 --> 00:15:54,386
Let’s not dwell on it
for the moment.

235
00:15:54,386 --> 00:15:56,988
So, what, are you having
second thoughts about Tara?

236
00:15:56,988 --> 00:15:58,990
There is something about Caleb.

237
00:15:58,990 --> 00:16:01,326
Something I cannot describe.

238
00:16:01,326 --> 00:16:04,596
- His blood.
- I’ve never inhaled
such a fragrance.

239
00:16:04,596 --> 00:16:06,198
Oh, he’s definitely appetizing.

240
00:16:06,198 --> 00:16:08,900
He is off-limits.
Do you all understand?

241
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:11,603
He is not to be harmed
in any way.

242
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:14,606
You think he’s the one.

243
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,176
Anything is possible.

244
00:16:20,712 --> 00:16:23,815
I must feed before tonight.

245
00:16:36,761 --> 00:16:38,563
- It’s getting late.
- Yeah.

246
00:16:38,563 --> 00:16:41,633
Trevor, where’s the spot
you’ve got all picked out?

247
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:43,935
Relax. It’s close.

248
00:16:43,935 --> 00:16:46,071
It’s worth the wait.

249
00:16:57,983 --> 00:17:00,852
[clicks teeth]
Wow.

250
00:17:00,852 --> 00:17:02,721
Isn’t this worth the wait?

251
00:17:03,822 --> 00:17:07,425
Speaking of waiting, Eli,

252
00:17:07,425 --> 00:17:11,096
you wanna know what I’ve
been waiting a long time for?

253
00:17:11,096 --> 00:17:12,197
What?

254
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:13,298
To kiss you.

255
00:17:13,298 --> 00:17:15,867
Whoa. Awkward.
What are you getting at?

256
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:17,669
I’m getting at

257
00:17:17,669 --> 00:17:20,672
