00:48:12,555 --> 00:48:16,526
I mean, don’t get me wrong.
I’m happy to be alive.

767
00:48:18,128 --> 00:48:19,562
But...

768
00:48:19,562 --> 00:48:21,464
Shall I start
from the beginning?

769
00:48:22,398 --> 00:48:24,534
They say that’s the best place.

770
00:48:25,702 --> 00:48:27,704
I’ll condense
some of the details.

771
00:48:27,704 --> 00:48:29,606
The story is as old as I.

772
00:48:29,606 --> 00:48:31,841
How old are you?

773
00:48:33,009 --> 00:48:35,945
I am forever frozen
at the age of 20.

774
00:48:35,945 --> 00:48:38,715
However, I have walked
the earth as a vampire

775
00:48:38,715 --> 00:48:40,617
for nearly 100 years.

776
00:48:43,119 --> 00:48:45,288
I’m all ears.

777
00:48:45,288 --> 00:48:48,525
Uh, nearly 100 years ago,

778
00:48:48,525 --> 00:48:51,528
an elder vampire named Naran

779
00:48:51,528 --> 00:48:54,430
found me near death,

780
00:48:54,430 --> 00:48:56,733
lying in a street.

781
00:48:56,733 --> 00:48:59,502
I do not even remember
the city, state

782
00:48:59,502 --> 00:49:01,471
or country I’m from.

783
00:49:01,471 --> 00:49:03,306
I remember his eyes,

784
00:49:03,306 --> 00:49:07,544
and then the pain
of his fangs in my neck.

785
00:49:07,544 --> 00:49:09,412
And the years passed.

786
00:49:09,412 --> 00:49:12,515
He and I were together as one.

787
00:49:12,515 --> 00:49:15,885
He filled my head with stories
of the elder vampires

788
00:49:15,885 --> 00:49:18,788
and their legends.

789
00:49:18,788 --> 00:49:22,425
He taught me everything
about being a vampire.

790
00:49:22,425 --> 00:49:24,828
He taught me to hunt.

791
00:49:34,003 --> 00:49:38,041
And he taught me about love.

792
00:49:45,181 --> 00:49:47,717
Have you--

793
00:49:47,717 --> 00:49:49,953
Have you ever killed?

794
00:49:49,953 --> 00:49:52,989
Another truth among the myths.

795
00:49:54,190 --> 00:49:57,927
Yes, vampires are sustained
by human blood.

796
00:49:57,927 --> 00:50:02,265
We can survive on animals
but only for so long.

797
00:50:02,265 --> 00:50:05,435
You said he taught you
about love.

798
00:50:05,435 --> 00:50:07,503
Yes.

799
00:50:07,503 --> 00:50:10,240
I was Naran’s chosen one.

800
00:50:10,240 --> 00:50:12,208
In order to stay immortal,

801
00:50:12,208 --> 00:50:16,312
an elder must choose
a companion,

802
00:50:16,312 --> 00:50:18,448
another who will complete them.

803
00:50:18,448 --> 00:50:21,050
Like yin and yang,
if you will.

804
00:50:21,951 --> 00:50:24,554
And you were his chosen one.

805
00:50:24,554 --> 00:50:27,156
I was for a time.

806
00:50:27,156 --> 00:50:30,460
As an elder vampire,
Naran would not be satisfied

807
00:50:30,460 --> 00:50:32,262
with only one mortal.

808
00:50:32,262 --> 00:50:35,365
Even after he turned me,
he was not fulfilled.

809
00:50:35,365 --> 00:50:36,900
He found another

810
00:50:36,900 --> 00:50:39,569
and turned her into a vampire.

811
00:50:42,672 --> 00:50:44,374
What happened to him?

812
00:50:44,374 --> 00:50:46,175
I have no idea.

813
00:50:46,175 --> 00:50:49,345
He left me in England,
and I have not seen him since.

814
00:50:51,648 --> 00:50:55,752
So, you think I’m
your chosen one?

815
00:50:57,120 --> 00:50:58,054
Yes.

816
00:50:59,222 --> 00:51:02,592
See, because I was turned
by an elder,

817
00:51:02,592 --> 00:51:04,827
I must do the same

818
00:51:04,827 --> 00:51:07,664
or I will not survive.

819
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:14,971
But I thought that vampires
were immortal.

820
00:51:14,971 --> 00:51:18,174
I mean, you are over
100 years old.

821
00:51:18,174 --> 00:51:19,976
Very true.

822
00:51:19,976 --> 00:51:22,578
However, without a companion,

823
00:51:22,578 --> 00:51:24,581
upon our 100th vampire year,

824
00:51:24,581 --> 00:51:26,683
we cease to exist.

825
00:51:28,151 --> 00:51:30,353
That’s a new one
to add to the list.

826
00:51:30,353 --> 00:51:32,822
Yes. Odd as it is,

827
00:51:32,822 --> 00:51:35,024
it is very true.

828
00:51:35,992 --> 00:51:38,394
What about mirrors?

829
00:51:39,896 --> 00:51:42,932
You think this hair
gets this way on its own?

830
00:51:42,932 --> 00:51:44,767
A mirror does help.

831
00:51:44,767 --> 00:51:47,036
- Crosses?
- As you can see,

832
00:51:47,036 --> 00:51:49,672
I’ve always been partial
to their religious significance.

833
00:51:49,672 --> 00:51:51,441
Garlic?

834
00:51:51,441 --> 00:51:52,775
Myth.

835
00:51:52,775 --> 00:51:54,777
Stake through the heart?

836
00:51:54,777 --> 00:51:56,679
You saw that a bullet
did not pierce my skin.

837
00:51:56,679 --> 00:52:00,249
Do you really think
a sharpened piece of wood
could do the trick?

838
00:52:00,249 --> 00:52:02,819
Point taken.

839
00:52:02,819 --> 00:52:04,621
As for the sun,

840
00:52:04,621 --> 00:52:07,890
we hybrids still have
some traces of human blood,

841
00:52:07,890 --> 00:52:11,427
so we’re not affected
by its rays.

842
00:52:11,427 --> 00:52:13,463
I don’t make the rules.

843
00:52:13,463 --> 00:52:17,500
Dane, Adam, and Logan
are also not affected.

844
00:52:17,500 --> 00:52:19,135
I created them.

845
00:52:20,703 --> 00:52:22,905
They’re vampires, too.

846
00:52:23,806 --> 00:52:25,808
We’re a small coven.

847
00:52:25,808 --> 00:52:27,810
I needed companions,

848
00:52:27,810 --> 00:52:29,812
and they have been aiding
in my journey

849
00:52:29,812 --> 00:52:31,514
for my eternal mate.

850
00:52:31,514 --> 00:52:33,416
Pretty tight group.

851
00:52:34,550 --> 00:52:37,320
Very much so.

852
00:52:38,421 --> 00:52:39,355
So...

853
00:52:43,292 --> 00:52:45,061
Yes?

854
00:52:46,462 --> 00:52:48,965
How do you kill a vampire?

855
00:52:48,965 --> 00:52:52,535
Why? Do you wanna kill me?

856
00:52:52,535 --> 00:52:54,203
No.

857
00:52:58,307 --> 00:53:03,446
Decapitation
is the only sure way.

858
00:53:05,948 --> 00:53:08,217
Decapitation.

859
00:53:09,419 --> 00:53:11,120
Uh...

860
00:53:12,755 --> 00:53:15,058
So what will happen to me?

861
00:53:15,058 --> 00:53:17,193
Are you going to turn me?

862
00:53:17,193 --> 00:53:21,130
Uh, yes,
it has come to that.

863
00:53:21,130 --> 00:53:24,000
I will not force you.

864
00:53:25,501 --> 00:53:28,471
If you feel for me

865
00:53:28,471 --> 00:53:31,707
the way I feel for you,

866
00:53:31,707 --> 00:53:34,343
you will choose
to be with me forever.

867
00:53:34,343 --> 00:53:36,512
And if not?

868
00:53:38,948 --> 00:53:41,918
Tara is aware of my true self.

869
00:53:41,918 --> 00:53:44,954
She was to be
the one originally.

870
00:53:44,954 --> 00:53:47,757
What happened?

871
00:53:47,757 --> 00:53:51,360
Truth be told,
you happened.

872
00:53:51,360 --> 00:53:53,863
I cannot explain it,

873
00:53:53,863 --> 00:53:56,299
but you have this tremendous
pull over me.

874
00:54:05,274 --> 00:54:08,711
So I would become a vampire.

875
00:54:08,711 --> 00:54:11,981
Yes, that is the idea.

876
00:54:15,718 --> 00:54:17,887
This is all too much.

877
00:54:19,122 --> 00:54:21,858
First, Paul goes missing,
and now this.

878
00:54:23,326 --> 00:54:25,561
How long do I have to decide?

879
00:54:25,561 --> 00:54:30,533
My 100th year as a vampire
is tomorrow, midnight.

880
00:54:30,533 --> 00:54:32,335
Are you kidding?

881
00:54:32,335 --> 00:54:34,804
I have to decide
in that short amount of time?

882
00:54:36,005 --> 00:54:38,174
I will not force you
to make any decision

883
00:54:38,174 --> 00:54:40,810
you do not want to.

884
00:54:43,579 --> 00:54:47,617
Look, I am aware
of the weight of all this.

885
00:54:47,617 --> 00:54:50,553
That is why I’m giving you
the choice.

886
00:54:50,553 --> 00:54:53,289
The choice I never had.

887
00:54:53,289 --> 00:54:56,926
You truly have no idea
the impact you’ve had on me.

888
00:54:59,262 --> 00:55:01,464
This is all happening
so fast.

889
00:55:02,932 --> 00:55:06,936
Why don’t you take a few hours
to think things over?

890
00:55:06,936 --> 00:55:09,305
I will honor your decision
either way.

891
00:55:11,073 --> 00:55:13,509
A few hours.

892
00:55:14,744 --> 00:55:18,281
I will leave you
to your thoughts.

893
00:55:18,281 --> 00:55:20,683
Wait.

894
00:55:20,683 --> 00:55:23,686
There’s so much to think about.

895
00:55:23,686 --> 00:55:25,822
How...

896
00:55:25,822 --> 00:55:27,557
What?

897
00:55:27,557 --> 00:55:31,194
I’m sorry for how quickly
this all came about.

898
00:55:31,194 --> 00:55:34,463
I wish there was more time.

899
00:55:37,967 --> 00:55:40,102
Can I call you tonight?

900
00:55:41,137 --> 00:55:43,406
That would be perfect.

901
00:55:50,546 --> 00:55:52,081
[sighs]

902
00:56:12,134 --> 00:56:14,737
You seem angry about something.

903
00:56:14,737 --> 00:56:16,739
You’re being foolish.

904
00:56:16,739 --> 00:56:18,274
How is that?

905
00:56:18,274 --> 00:56:20,710
You’re not thinking clearly.

906
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:22,712
Tara is the one.

907
00:56:22,712 --> 00:56:25,681
I chose her myself.
You were happy with her.

908
00:56:25,681 --> 00:56:29,585
Yes, but my heart
knew differently.

909
00:56:29,585 --> 00:56:32,154
I cannot explain it.

910
00:56:32,154 --> 00:56:34,357
So you’ve said.

911
00:56:34,357 --> 00:56:36,559
You’re being ridiculous.

912
00:56:36,559 --> 00:56:40,029
Your time, my time

913
00:56:40,029 --> 00:56:42,131
is almost over.

914
00:56:42,131 --> 00:56:45,134
I’m aware of what could happen.

915
00:56:45,134 --> 00:56:47,937
If Caleb decides
this is too much for him,

916
00:56:47,937 --> 00:56:51,107
I will accept Tara as the one
and turn her tomorrow.

917
00:56:51,107 --> 00:56:52,808
Why can’t you do it now?

918
00:56:52,808 --> 00:56:56,112
Why must you wait
till the last possible minute?

919
00:56:56,112 --> 00:56:58,114
It is my decision.

920
00:56:58,114 --> 00:57:01,117
I am aware
of the ramifications.

921
00:57:01,117 --> 00:57:04,720
We die, too!

922
00:57:04,720 --> 00:57:07,990
You know that, right?

923
00:57:07,990 --> 00:57:12,028
This is not just about you.

924
00:57:12,028 --> 00:57:16,565
I think you should calm down.

925
00:57:17,667 --> 00:57:19,802
[Logan]
How am I supposed to calm down

926
00:57:19,802 --> 00:57:21,804
when my life’s in danger?

927
00:57:21,804 --> 00:57:24,073
Caleb is a plaything.

928
00:57:24,073 --> 00:57:27,076
Tara is the one.

929
00:57:27,076 --> 00:57:31,414
Why?
Because you say she is?

930
00:57:34,817 --> 00:57:36,719
[hisses]

931
00:57:39,622 --> 00:57:41,991
Are you sure
you wanna go there?

932
00:57:41,991 --> 00:57:44,026
What’s the problem, guys?

933
00:57:44,026 --> 00:57:46,562
I’m not afraid of you.

934
00:57:47,630 --> 00:57:51,567
You do not want
to die now, do you?

935
00:57:51,567 --> 00:57:54,236
[chuckling]

936
00:57:54,236 --> 00:57:57,340
Are you threatening me?

937
00:57:57,340 --> 00:58:01,610
You initiated this,
and I will gladly finish it.

938
00:58:01,610 --> 00:58:03,612
[hisses]

939
00:58:03,612 --> 00:58:06,482
- Back away.
- Let’s not lose our heads.

940
00:58:06,482 --> 00:58:09,585
Logan, if Caleb is the one
that Jasin wants, let it be.

941
00:58:09,585 --> 00:58:14,890
Jasin is willing to let us die
for a piece of meat.

942
00:58:14,890 --> 00:58:16,492
Break it up.

943
00:58:18,094 --> 00:58:20,496
Now.

944
00:58:26,068 --> 00:58:28,337
This isn’t over.

945
00:58:35,144 --> 00:58:37,913
This can’t be good.

946
00:58:37,913 --> 00:58:40,716
He just needs to calm down.

947
00:58:40,716 --> 00:58:44,019
Do you think he meant it--
it not being over?

948
00:58:44,019 --> 00:58:46,021
Is-- Is he gonna try something?

949
00:58:46,021 --> 00:58:48,524
I cannot be certain.

950
00:58:48,524 --> 00:58:49,525
[answering machine beeps]

951
00:58:49,525 --> 00:58:51,527
Hey, Jasin, it’s Caleb.

952
00:58:51,527 --> 00:58:55,398
Um, I just really
would like to see you.

953
00:58:55,398 --> 00:58:58,501
Can you come over
when you get his?

954
00:59:04,273 --> 00:59:07,343
Did I keep you waiting?

955
00:59:07,343 --> 00:59:09,345
Were you out here
the whole time?

956
00:59:09,345 --> 00:59:11,547
I was across town.

957
00:59:11,547 --> 00:59:12,882
Serious?

958
00:59:12,882 --> 00:59:15,351
Another perk of being a vampire.

959
00:59:18,754 --> 00:59:20,356
What’s wrong?

960
00:59:21,424 --> 00:59:23,459
You have to invite me in.

961
00:59:23,459 --> 00:59:26,061
- Really?
- I know.

962
00:59:26,061 --> 00:59:27,930
Another very old vampire myth.

963
00:59:27,930 --> 00:59:31,200
However, it is one of the few
we hybrids must follow.

964
00:59:31,200 --> 00:59:34,136
But you were in my backyard.

965
00:59:34,136 --> 00:59:36,906
That was outdoors.

966
00:59:36,906 --> 00:59:39,375
It was not where you live.

967
00:59:39,375 --> 00:59:41,243
I don’t make the rules.

968
00:59:42,144 --> 00:59:44,246
I invite you in.

969
00:59:58,561 --> 01:00:02,198
Have you given
any more thought
to our earlier discussion?

970
01:00:02,198 --> 01:00:03,933
I have,

971
01:00:03,933 --> 01:00:06,469
but I’ve been
a little distracted.

972
01:00:06,469 --> 01:00:08,471
Paul isn’t answering his phone.

973
01:00:08,471 --> 01:00:10,206
I think he’s ignoring me.

974
01:00:10,206 --> 01:00:12,041
Didn’t you two have a fight?

975
01:00:12,041 --> 01:00:13,843
You could say that,

976
01:00:13,843 --> 01:00:16,278
but it seems
a little unlike him.

977
01:00:17,513 --> 01:00:19,482
You haven’t known him that long.

978
01:00:19,482 --> 01:00:21,417
Maybe it is just like him.

979
01:00:23,752 --> 01:00:28,157
So, about our
earlier conversation.

980
01:00:29,425 --> 01:00:32,294
There’s just so much
to consider.

981
01:00:33,529 --> 01:00:36,432
What are your feelings
for me?

982
01:00:36,432 --> 01:00:38,434
It’s funny.

983
01:00:38,434 --> 01:00:40,836
I’ve never felt this way
about anyone,

984
01:00:40,836 --> 01:00:42,838
ever.

985
01:00:42,838 --> 01:00:44,673
I feel the same.

986
01:00:46,308 --> 01:00:48,544
What about Tara?

987
01:00:48,544 --> 01:00:52,681
If she truly were the one,
I would not be here right now.

988
01:00:58,420 --> 01:01:00,956
Would you give yourself
to me freely?

989
01:01:03,225 --> 01:01:04,693
I...

990
01:01:04,693 --> 01:01:06,295
[knock at door]

991
01:01:13,402 --> 01:01:15,871
What’s going on?

992
01:01:15,871 --> 01:01:18,440
- Big trouble.
- That’s putting it mildly.

993
01:01:18,440 --> 01:01:20,109
What are you both talking about?

994
01:01:20,109 --> 01:01:21,710
Logan has completely lost it.

995
01:01:21,710 --> 01:01:24,547
- What’s going on?
- Hey, Caleb.

996
01:01:24,547 --> 01:01:27,416
- So, ready to become one of us?
- Stay focused, Dane.

997
01:01:27,416 --> 01:01:30,653
- What has happened?
What’s Logan done?
- Logan has taken Tara.

998
01:01:30,653 --> 01:01:33,522
He sent us to find you.
If you don’t meet him
tonight in the meadow,

999
01:01:33,522 --> 01:01:36,792
he’s gonna kill her,
and he’s gonna hunt you down
and kill you, too.

1000
01:01:36,792 --> 01:01:38,727
What? Wait.

1001
01:01:38,727 --> 01:01:40,663
No. Sorry, man. We don’t have
enough time to explain.

1002
01:01:40,663 --> 01:01:42,598
Oh, you should’ve seen him.

1003
01:01:42,598 --> 01:01:47,469
We couldn’t stop him.
He’s more powerful
than either of us.

1004
01:01:47,469 --> 01:01:49,905
May they come in?

1005
01:01:49,905 --> 01:01:53,776
Yes, of course.
You can both come in.

1006
01:01:55,711 --> 01:01:59,248
- Logan has taken this too far.
- You should’ve seen
the look in his eyes.

1007
01:01:59,248 --> 01:02:02,585
- Oh, darker than normal.
- I will not fight him
unless I must.

1008
01:02:02,585 --> 01:02:04,720
I cannot let him harm Tara.

1009
01:02:04,720 --> 01:02:08,257
Is he more powerful than you?
I don’t wanna lose you.

1010
01:02:08,257 --> 01:02:10,259
I created Logan.

1011
01:02:10,259 --> 01:02:12,194
He was my first transformation.

1012
01:02:12,194 --> 01:02:14,163
He is a very powerful vampire.

1013
01:02:14,163 --> 01:02:17,166
- He threw Adam through a tree.
- It didn’t hurt.

1014
01:02:17,166 --> 01:02:19,635
Stay focused, guys.

1015
01:02:19,635 --> 01:02:22,671
If he wants me to meet him,
so be it.

1016
01:02:22,671 --> 01:02:24,673
You must stay behind.

1017
01:02:24,673 --> 01:02:27,409
Bullshit.
I’m not staying here.

1018
01:02:27,409 --> 01:02:29,345
You are a stubborn one,
aren’t you?

1019
01:02:29,345 --> 01:02:31,714
Damn straight.
I don’t wanna lose you.

1020
01:02:31,714 --> 01:02:33,315
Don’t worry, Jasin.

1021
01:02:33,315 --> 01:02:35,751
We’ll help protect him.

1022
01:02:35,751 --> 01:02:38,153
If we don’t die
in the process.

1023
01:02:38,153 --> 01:02:41,090
I do not think that Logan
means to hurt Tara.

1024
01:02:41,090 --> 01:02:43,459
It is more than likely
a plot to get Caleb.

1025
01:02:43,459 --> 01:02:45,461
Caleb is the true target.

1026
01:02:45,461 --> 01:02:47,062
You must stay here.

1027
01:02:50,966 --> 01:02:52,901
So be it.

1028
01:03:01,710 --> 01:03:03,545
